:INFO
Synth Repair Tools and Test Equipment
A practical toolkit for diagnosing and repairing vintage analog synthesizers. You do not need everything at once. Start with the basics and add as your projects grow.

:TASK
[ ] Digital multimeter (Fluke or UNI-T)
[ ] Soldering iron with fine tip (Hakko or similar)
[ ] Solder (60/40 or lead-free)
[ ] Desoldering pump or wick
[ ] Oscilloscope (Rigol DS1054Z is entry level)
[ ] Isopropyl alcohol 99 percent and brushes
[ ] Contact cleaner spray (DeoxIT D5)
[ ] Tweezers and plastic spudgers
[ ] Service manual printed or on tablet

:NOTE
An oscilloscope is not required for basic pot cleaning and cap replacement but becomes essential when tracing audio signal faults or calibrating oscillators. A used Rigol scope costs around 300 USD and covers most synth work.

